    "It has been shown, for example, that tumor samples which contain a large number of heterogeneous cell states require a high number of FOV for adequate analysis [167].Not all technologies are compatible with all samples.",
    "While they are more widely available, samples preserved in FFPE can be more challenging to assay as these samples tend to suffer from increased RNA fragmentation and increased modifications of proteins and metabolites.",
    "A further consideration is the species of interest.",
    "Spatial multi-omic methods can in principle be applied to any kind tissue, but hybridization-based technologies such as Visium v2 or Xenium rely on the construction of probes, which are only available for human and mouse samples currently.After a technology has been chosen, it is generally necessary to optimize the processing of samples.",
    "Different tissues can be more or less challenging and require different treatment, owing to factors such as ease of permeabilization, resistance to proteinase, or increased autofluorescence."
